    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Electrical or mechanical systems, installed in a building that sound a blast or bell when smoke or flames are detected; certain alarms are engineered to trigger sprinkler systems for added protection.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000027101/Smit, Means Illustrated Construction Dictionary (1985)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Sistemas eléctricos o mecánicos instalados en un edificio, que hacen sonar una alarma o campana cuando humo o llamas son detectadas; ciertas alarmas son diseñadas para accionar sistemas de rociadores, como protección adicional.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Elektrische of mechanische systemen die in een gebouw zijn geïnstalleerd en een bel of luchtstoot ten gehore brengen wanneer er rook of vlammen worden bespeurd. Bepaalde alarmen zijn uitgerust om sproeisystemen in werking te stellen voor extra bescherming.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>裝置在建築物內部的電子或機械系統，當偵測到煙霧或火焰時會發出聲響或響鈴；有些警鈴設計會啟動灑水系統，加強防護作用。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
